ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: When I am distressed or upset by things, I am motivated to engage and work with my distress when it arises
When I am distressed or upset by things, I notice, and am sensitive to my distressed feelings when they arise in me
When I am distressed or upset by things, I avoid thinking about my distress and try to distract myself and put it out of my mind
Notes: 1=Never; 10=Always; Note item is reversed and is not included in scoring

ElementDescription: When I am distressed or upset by things, I am emotionally moved by my distressed feelings or situations
When I am distressed or upset by things, I tolerate the various feelings that are part of my distress
When I am distressed or upset by things, I reflect on and make sense of my feelings of distress
When I am distressed or upset by things, I do not tolerate being distressed
Notes: 1=Never; 10=Always; Note item is reversed and is not included in scoring

ElementDescription: When I am distressed or upset by things, I am accepting, non-critical and non-judgmental of my feelings of distress
When I am distressed or upset by things, I direct my attention to what is likely to be helpful to me
When I am distressed or upset by things, I think about and come up with helpful ways to cope with my distress
When I am distressed or upset by things, I don't know how to help myself
Notes: 1=Never; 10=Always; Note item is reversed and is not included in scoring

ElementDescription: When I am distressed or upset by things, I take the actions and do the things that will be helpful to me
When I am distressed or upset by things, I create inner feelings of support, helpfulness and encouragement
Self-compassion - Engagement Subscore
Self-compassion - Actions Subscore
Self-compassion - Total Score
When others are distressed or upset by things, I am motivated to engage and work with other peoples' distress when it arises
When others are distressed or upset by things, I notice and am sensitive to distress in others when it arises
When others are distressed or upset by things, I avoid thinking about other peoples' distress, try to distract myself and put it out of my mind
Notes: 1=Never; 10=Always; Note item is reversed and is not included in scoring

ElementDescription: When others are distressed or upset by things, I am emotionally moved by expressions of distress in others
When others are distressed or upset by things, I tolerate the various feelings that are part of other people's distress
When others are distressed or upset by things, I reflect on and make sense of other people's distress
When others are distressed or upset by things, I do not tolerate other peoples' distress
Notes: 1=Never; 10=Always; Note item is reversed and is not included in scoring

ElementDescription: When others are distressed or upset by things, I am accepting, non-critical and non-judgmental of others people's distress
When others are distressed or upset by things, I direct attention to what is likely to be helpful to others
When others are distressed or upset by things, I think about and come up with helpful ways for them to cope with their distress
When others are distressed or upset by things, I don't know how to help other people when they are distressed
Notes: 1=Never; 10=Always; Note item is reversed and is not included in scoring

ElementDescription: When others are distressed or upset by things, I take the actions and do the things that will be helpful to others
When others are distressed or upset by things, I express feelings of support, helpfulness and encouragement to others
Compassion to Others - Engagement Subscore
Notes: Sum of compassion to others items 1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 8

ElementDescription: Compassion to Others - Actions Subscore
Notes: Sum of compassion to others items 9, 10, 12, 13

ElementDescription: Compassion to Others - Total Score
Notes: Sum of compassion to others items 1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 8, 9, 10, 12, 13
